{{Infobox journal | title = Clinical Social Work Journal | cover = | editor = Carol Tosone | discipline = [[Social work]] | abbreviation = Clin. Soc. Work J. | publisher = [[Springer Science+Business Media]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1973-present | impact = 0.494 | impact-year = 2012 | website = https://www.springer.com/psychology/journal/10615 | link1 = https://link.springer.com/journal/10615 | link1-name = Online access | ISSN = 0091-1674 | eISSN = 1573-3343 | OCLC = 299333432 | LCCN = 73643802 }} The '''''Clinical Social Work Journal''''' is a quarterly, [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes articles, commentaries, and [[book review]]s relevant to contemporary [[clinical social work]] practice, research, theory, and policy. It is currently published by [[Springer Science+Business Media]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Carol Tosone. The journal was established in 1973. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2012 [[impact factor]] of 0.494.<ref name="WoS">{{cite book |year=2013 |chapter=Clinical Social Work Journal |title=2012 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
