{{Infobox body of water | name = Hamlagrøvatnet | other_name = | image = Hamlagrovatnet smt.jpg | alt = | caption = Hamlagrøvatnet at wintertime (behind the trees) | image_bathymetry = | alt_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Voss]] and [[Kvam]], [[Hordaland]] | coords = {{coord|60.5523|6.1541|region:NO_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}} | type = | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = [[Norway]] | date-built = | date-flooded = | length = {{convert|10|km}} | width = {{convert|1.8|km}} | area = {{convert|9.96|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = {{convert|28.01|km|abbr=on}} | elevation = {{convert|588|m}} | frozen = | islands = | cities = | reference = [[Norwegian Water Resources and Energy Directorate|NVE]] }}
'''Hamlagrøvatnet''' is a [[lake]] on the border of the municipalities of [[Voss]] and [[Kvam]] in [[Hordaland]] county, [[Norway]]. The {{convert|10.3|km2|adj=on}} lake is the largest lake in all of Hordaland county. The lake is located about {{convert|17|km}} southeast of the village of [[Dalekvam]] and about {{convert|10|km}} south of the village of [[Evanger (village)|Evanger]].
The lake sits at the eastern end of the [[Bergsdalen]] valley and it is regulated at elevation of {{convert|588|to|560|m}} above sea level. The lake is a reservoir on the river Bergsdalselvi which has four [[hydroelectric]] power stations on it. The lake is surrounded by many [[holiday cottage]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hordaland.no/om-hordaland/Fakta-om-Hordaland/|title=Fakta om Hordaland|publisher=Hordaland.no|accessdate=2013-04-04|language=Norwegian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130914180434/http://www.hordaland.no/om-hordaland/Fakta-om-Hordaland/|archivedate=2013-09-14|df=}}</ref><ref name="snl">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/Hamlagr%C3%B8vatnet|title=Hamlagrøvatnet|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2014-05-14}}</ref>
