The '''Medical Association of Georgia''' ('''MAG''') is an organization in [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] that advocates for physicians in the state. Established in 1849, it is an affiliate of the [[American Medical Association]], and it has over 7,800 members.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/07/georgias-doctors-and-the-ethics-of-execution/260083/ | title=Georgia's Doctors and the Ethics of Execution | work=The Atlantic | date=20 July 2012 | accessdate=31 January 2016 | author=Vox, Ford}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mag.org/about-us/ | title=About Us | work=Medical Association of Georgia | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref> Since 1911, the MAG has published a quarterly journal, the '''''Journal of the Medical Association of Georgia'''''.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.mag.org/georgia/Public/Publications/Journal/Public/Publications/Journal_of_the_Medical_Association_of_Georgia/Journal.aspx?hkey=d95e9603-061b-4515-9938-54245a3fa322 | title=MAG's quarterly, members-only journal is celebrating 100 years of in-depth excellence | work=MAG website | accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://journalseek.net/cgi-bin/journalseek/journalsearch.cgi?field=issn&query=0025-7028 |title=Journal of the Medical Association of Georgia |website=journalseek.net |access-date=2017-11-27}}</ref>

The MAG conducts regular annual sessions where the officers, members and delegates meet over several days. Between 1880 and 1910, most of these sessions were held in [[Atlanta]], [[Augusta, Georgia | Augusta]] and [[Macon, Georgia | Macon]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://archive.org/search.php?query=-title%3A%28Journal%29+AND+creator%3A%28Medical+Association+of+Georgia%29&sort=date | title=Transactions of Medical Association of Georgia | work=archive.org | accessdate=4 November 2017}}</ref>

