The '''Ministry of Health and Social Welfare''' is a [[government ministry]] of the [[Republic of Liberia]]. In June 2015 [[Bernice Dahn]] became the Health Minister. <ref>{{Cite web|title=FrontPageAfrica - Dr. Bernice Dahn Finally Confirmed As Health Minister |url=http://www.frontpageafricaonline.com/index.php/news/5540-dr-bernice-dahn-finally-confirmed-as-health-minister |website=www.frontpageafricaonline.com |accessdate=2015-08-04 |first= |last=Webmaster |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150801213457/http://www.frontpageafricaonline.com/index.php/news/5540-dr-bernice-dahn-finally-confirmed-as-health-minister |archivedate=2015-08-01 |df= }}</ref> Dahn succeeded Dr. [[Walter Gwenigale]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dw.de/liberias-health-minister-more-people-beginning-to-believe-ebola-is-real/a-17861507|title=Liberia's health minister: 'More people beginning to believe Ebola is real'|date=2014-08-18|author=Asumpta Lattus|publisher=Deutsche Welle}}</ref>

{{As of|2014}}, the ministry is engaged in a major public health campaign to control the [[Ebola virus epidemic in West Africa|Ebola virus epidemic]] in Liberia.

